item.description:
By using INHIBIT along with ALTER command, we can have a read-only VSAM dataset.
Example:
//STEP1 EXEC PGM=IDCAMS //SYSPRINT DD SYSOUT=* //SYSIN DD * ALTER – SECRET.KSDS.DATA – INHIBIT ALTER – SECRET.KSDS.INDEX – INHIBIT /*  Notice that the ALTER command is used with DATA and INDEX and not with the cluster.

In general we use DUMMY datasets in JCL instead of a actual file for some requirements.
But how can we specify dummy VSAM dataset in a JCL?
The parameter AMP=&lsquo;AMORG&rsquo; tells the OS to treat the file as VSAM file.
 //NOVSAMIO DD DUMMY,AMP=&lsquo;AMORG&rsquo;
